# ============================================================
# Globe AMS — 07. Token Management
# ============================================================
# Refresh token rotation, revocation, forgot-password flow,
# and logout (cookie clearing).
#
# The access token is short-lived (120 min in dev, 60 min in prod).
# Refresh tokens are single-use (rotation) and expire in 7 days.
# ============================================================

@baseUrl = http://localhost:5006

# Paste from 01_admin-auth.http login response:
@accessToken  = PASTE_ACCESS_JWT_HERE
@refreshToken = PASTE_REFRESH_TOKEN_HERE

### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### 1. Refresh access token (happy path)
### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# @name refreshResult
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/refresh
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "accessToken": "{{accessToken}}",
  "refreshToken": "{{refreshToken}}"
}

###
# ✅ Expected 200 — new accessToken + new refreshToken
# Old refreshToken is invalidated (rotation policy).
# New HTTP-only cookie is also set if cookie auth is used.

### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### 2. Reuse the OLD refresh token after rotation (expect 401)
### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# The refresh token from step 0 was consumed in step 1.
# Using it again must be rejected (prevents replay attacks).
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/refresh
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "accessToken": "{{accessToken}}",
  "refreshToken": "{{refreshToken}}"
}

###
# ❌ Expected 400 Bad Request — refresh token already used (revoked/replaced by rotation)

### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### 3. Refresh with invalid/garbage token (expect 401)
### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/refresh
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "accessToken": "{{accessToken}}",
  "refreshToken": "completely-invalid-token-garbage"
}

###
# ❌ Expected 401 Unauthorized

### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### 4. Revoke a specific refresh token (requires auth)
### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Use the new tokens obtained from step 1 (refreshResult):
@newAccessToken  = PASTE_NEW_ACCESS_TOKEN_FROM_STEP_1
@newRefreshToken = PASTE_NEW_REFRESH_TOKEN_FROM_STEP_1

POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/revoke
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{newAccessToken}}

"{{newRefreshToken}}"

###
# ✅ Expected 204 — token revoked
# Note: body is a raw JSON string (not an object), matching [FromBody] string token

### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### 5. Attempt to use the revoked refresh token (expect 401)
### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/refresh
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "accessToken": "{{newAccessToken}}",
  "refreshToken": "{{newRefreshToken}}"
}

###
# ❌ Expected 400 Bad Request — token was explicitly revoked in step 4

### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### 6. Revoke without auth (expect 401)
### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/revoke
Content-Type: application/json

"some-refresh-token"

###
# ❌ Expected 401 Unauthorized — [Authorize] required

### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### 7. Forgot password — existing email (anti-enumeration)
### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/forgot-password
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "admin@globe.com"
}

###
# ✅ Expected 200 OK
# Check console logs for the reset token printed by the email stub:
#   [Email] To: admin@globe.com | Subject: Reset Your Password
#   Body: ...?token=<URL_ENCODED_TOKEN>&email=...

### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### 8. Forgot password — non-existent email (anti-enumeration: always 200)
### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/forgot-password
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "doesnotexist@ghost.com"
}

###
# ✅ Expected 200 — same response regardless of email existence
# ✓ Cannot enumerate registered emails through this endpoint

### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### 9. Reset password (use token from step 7 console logs)
### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/reset-password
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "admin@globe.com",
  "token": "PASTE_RESET_TOKEN_FROM_CONSOLE_LOGS",
  "newPassword": "NewAdmin@456!",
  "confirmPassword": "NewAdmin@456!"
}

###
# ✅ Expected 200 — password changed

### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### 10. Login with new password to confirm reset worked
### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "admin@globe.com",
  "password": "NewAdmin@456!",
  "tenantSlug": "globe"
}

###
# ✅ Expected 200 — login succeeds with new password

### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### 11. Reset password with mismatched confirm (expect 400)
### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/reset-password
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "admin@globe.com",
  "token": "PASTE_RESET_TOKEN",
  "newPassword": "NewAdmin@456!",
  "confirmPassword": "DifferentPassword@999!"
}

###
# ❌ Expected 400 Bad Request — FluentValidation: passwords must match

### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### 12. Logout (clears HTTP-only cookie)
### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/logout
Authorization: Bearer {{newAccessToken}}

###
# ✅ Expected 200 — access_token cookie deleted from browser
# Note: the JWT bearer token itself remains valid until expiry.
# Always revoke the refresh token (step 4) alongside logout
# to prevent re-authentication via token refresh.

### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### 13. Logout without auth (expect 401)
### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/logout

###
# ❌ Expected 401 Unauthorized — [Authorize] required
